# Cursor AI Rules for NEO Monorepo

## Project Overview
This is a monorepo containing an AI Agent Platform built with:
- `apps/web`: Next.js 14 web application
- `apps/api`: NestJS API application with TypeScript
- `packages/shared`: Shared utilities and components
- PostgreSQL database with Prisma ORM
- Authentication with JWT and 2FA
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui for styling

## Code Style & Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript configuration
- Prefer explicit types over `any`
- Use interfaces for object shapes, types for unions/primitives
- Always include proper JSDoc comments for public APIs
- Use class-validator for DTO validation
- Use class-transformer for data transformation

### React/Next.js (Frontend)
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer `useState` and `useEffect` over class components
- Use Next.js 14 App Router patterns
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use React.memo() for expensive components
- Follow the "children as props" pattern for flexible components

### NestJS (Backend)
- Follow NestJS decorator patterns
- Use dependency injection for services
- Implement proper guards for authentication
- Use interceptors for request/response transformation
- Use pipes for validation
- Use custom decorators for metadata
- Follow module-based architecture
- Use proper exception filters for error handling

### File Organization
- Use kebab-case for file names
- Group related files in feature folders
- Keep components close to where they're used
- Use index files for clean imports
- Separate business logic from UI components
- Follow NestJS module structure: controllers, services, DTOs, entities

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `UserProfile.tsx`)
- Files: kebab-case (e.g., `user-profile.tsx`)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., `getUserData`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `API_ENDPOINTS`)
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase (e.g., `UserProfile`)
- NestJS Controllers: PascalCase with 'Controller' suffix (e.g., `UsersController`)
- NestJS Services: PascalCase with 'Service' suffix (e.g., `UsersService`)
- DTOs: PascalCase with 'Dto' suffix (e.g., `CreateUserDto`)

## Architecture Guidelines

### Monorepo Structure
- Keep shared code in `packages/shared`
- Use workspace dependencies for internal packages
- Maintain clear boundaries between apps
- Use Turbo for build orchestration
- NestJS API in `apps/api` with module-based structure

### Database & API (NestJS)
- Use Prisma for database operations
- Implement proper error handling in controllers
- Use class-validator for DTO validation
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Implement proper authentication guards
- Use interceptors for response transformation
- Use exception filters for error handling
- Implement proper logging with NestJS Logger

### State Management
- Use React Context for global state sparingly
- Prefer local state with useState/useReducer
- Use SWR or React Query for server state
- Keep state as close to where it's used as possible

## Security Best Practices

### Authentication & Authorization
- Always validate JWT tokens with NestJS guards
- Implement proper role-based access control
- Use secure session management
- Sanitize user inputs
- Implement rate limiting with NestJS interceptors
- Use Passport.js strategies for authentication

### Data Protection
- Never expose sensitive data in client-side code
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Implement proper CORS policies
- Validate all API inputs with class-validator
- Use encryption for sensitive data

